OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy start with rain clearing
OL,6,Fto the north. Brightening up, with
OL,7,Fsunny spells but also the risk of
OL,8,Fshowers developing. These likely to be
OL,9,Fheavy, perhaps with thunder and hail
OL,10,Fin the south.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FShowers gradually easing
OL,13,Fduring the evening but lingering for
OL,14,Fmuch of the night in places. Remaining
OL,15,Flargely cloudy and generally mild.
OL,16,
OL,17,CMonday:FA cloudy start for many on
OL,18,FMonday. Perhaps a few brighter spells
OL,19,Femerging later. A continued risk of
OL,20,Fshowers in the south. Temperatures
OL,21,Fclose to normal for early May.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
